Hello!

Would you like a Hello World example in a specific language? Here are quick options:

- Python: print("Hello, World!")
- JavaScript: console.log("Hello, World!")
- C: #include <stdio.h> int main(void) { printf("Hello, World!"); return 0; }
- Java: public class HelloWorld { public static void main(String[] args) { System.out.println("Hello, World!"); } }
- Go: package main; import "fmt"; func main() { fmt.Println("Hello, World!") }

Tell me your preferred language (or share another), and I’ll tailor it.

